[h1]Start in an Isolated Extra-Galactic Constellations[/h1]
This mod takes the excellent constellations from [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=1523039190]Extra Galactic Clusters[/url] and makes it possible to have any of them as a starting location for your civilisation.

It is done via Civic or an Origin: Extra-Galatic Cluster (take the one that combines best with your playstyle).
If your civilisation takes that then a menu will appear on game start for you to customise your cluster.  The AI never will. 

[h1]Gameplay[/h1]
Your civilisation will move into its new cluster home on day 2 to avoid issues with galaxy generation.  Select your options then start time, the game will freeze and lag while it generates the cluster, which might take a while on large galaxies, be patient, it will start.  Guarenteed habitable worlds and strategic resources happen a few days after.

Your constellation will not have precursors.  If you want to learn about your precursor civilisation you will need to get back to your
You can Experimental Subspace Navigation your science vessels to your old home system (and L-Gates if selected), that is deliberate.

This mod was also inspired by [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=1796380598]Isolated Cluster Start[/url]

In multiplayer you should all take different clusters.

[h1]Compatibility[/h1]
No vanilla files were harmed in the making of this mod, as it moves your home system it should be /mostly/ compatible with most origins.  It will not work well with things that involve your empire cluster, like Hegemony starts.

It will now work for any weird starting systems you like that happen from origins.  

Compatible with [url=https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=865040033]Guillis Planet Modifiers[/url].

